cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper is about generating random parameters in feedforward neural networks, which is a topic closely related to neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the drawbacks of the standard method and proposes a new method to improve it, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the importance of modeling target function nonlinearity, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of activation functions in modeling, which is relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
